        }
      }
    ],
    "leadingComments": [
      "/*\n\n    This is the unexpected behavior due to setting max_insert_delayed_streams_for_parallel_write > 1.\n\n    This unexpected behavior was present since version 21.9 or earlier but due to this PR https://github.com/ClickHouse/ClickHouse/pull/34780\n    when max_insert_delayed_streams_for_parallel_write gets disabled by default the issue was mitigated.\n\n    This is what happens:\n\n    - 1st insert works for landing and mv tables\n    - 2nd insert gets first block 20220901 deduplicated and second one inserted in landing table\n    - 2nd insert is not inserting anything in mv table due to a bug computing blocks to be discarded, now that block is inserted because deduplicate_blocks_in_dependent_materialized_views=0\n\n    Now it is fixed.\n*/"
    ]
  },
  {
    "kind": "set",
    "settings": [
      {
        "name": "deduplicate_blocks_in_dependent_materialized_views",
        "value": {
          "kind": "literal",
          "type": "UInt64",
          "value": "1"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "max_insert_delayed_streams_for_parallel_write",
        "value": {
          "kind": "literal",
          "type": "UInt64",
          "value": "1000"
        }
      }
    ],
    "leadingComments": [
      "/*\n\n    By setting deduplicate_blocks_in_dependent_materialized_views = 1 we can make the code go through a different path getting an expected\n    behavior again, even with max_insert_delayed_streams_for_parallel_write > 1.\n\n    This is what happens now:\n\n    - 1st insert works for landing and mv tables\n    - 2nd insert gets first block 20220901 deduplicated for landing and both rows are inserted for mv tables\n\n*/"
    ]
  },
